    <summary>AI-powered git commit assistant</summary>
    <description>
gix generates conventional commit messages from your staged git diff using AI.

## Features

- Generates Conventional Commits from staged diffs
- `gix split` splits a large diff into multiple semantic commits
- Embedding-based hunk clustering for intelligent grouping
- Multiple AI providers: OpenAI, Gemini, or Ollama (fully local/offline)
- Single binary, no runtime dependencies

## Usage

```
git add .
gix commit
```

You will see a suggested message and can accept, edit, regenerate, or cancel.

## Configuration

```
gix config set-provider openai     # default
gix config set-provider gemini
gix config set-provider ollama     # local, no API key required
gix config set-key                 # set OpenAI key
gix config set-key --provider gemini
```
    </description>
    <releaseNotes>https://github.com/ademajagon/gix/releases/tag/v0.3.0</releaseNotes>
